"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923444","Treasury","false","2018-06-18","<p>As has been the convention of successive governments, details of conversations between Secretaries of State are not normally disclosed.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","153307","2018-06-18T13:14:42.513Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923444/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923444/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923444/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-06-13","Trident: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what discussions he has had with the Secretary of State for Defence on the relative fiscal multiplier of the trident weapons programme relative to other (a) army, (b) navy and (c) air force expenditure in Scotland.","false","Biography information for Drew Hendry","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Drew Hendry","153377"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923445","Treasury","false","2018-06-18","<p>Treasury Ministers and officials receive representations from a wide variety of organisations in the public and private sectors as part of the process of policy development and delivery.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","153308","2018-06-18T13:06:19.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923445/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923445/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923445/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-06-13","Public Expenditure: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what representations his Department has received from business organisations and trade unions on changes to the Scottish Government block grant since 2010; and to how many of these has his Department responded.","false","Biography information for Drew Hendry","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Drew Hendry","153378"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923447","Treasury","false","2018-06-18","<p>The number of senior civil servants employed at HM Treasury in 2008/09 was 109, in 2009/10 it was 125</p><p> </p><p>The number of senior civil servants employed at HM Treasury Group since 2010/11 can be found in the annual report and accounts which can be accessed via this link: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-annual-report" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-annual-report</a></p><p>The number for each year can be found in the following pages of the corresponding annual report and accounts: 10/11- Page 44 11/12- page 48 12/13- page 44 13/14- page 48 14/15- page 193 15/16- page 82 16/17- page 74 17/18- due to be published shortly</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2018-06-18T15:36:48.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923447/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923447/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923447/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-06-13","Treasury: Senior Civil Servants","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many senior civil servants (a) are employed and (b) have been employed in each of the last 10 years in his Department.","false","Biography information for Chris Law","Dundee West","Chris Law","153334"
