"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922377","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-06-19","<p>​We remain very concerned about all our dual nationals detained in Iran. We continue to raise their cases with the Iranian government at every opportunity, and make decisions in line with what we believe will produce the best outcomes in their cases. However, we will not be providing a continuous commentary. We judge this will not be helpful, or in the best interest of each case.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-06-19T15:22:03.67Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922377/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922377/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922377/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-06-12","Nazanin Zaghari-Ratcliffe","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps the Government is taking to secure the immediate release of Nazanin Zaghari-Ratcliffe.","false","Biography information for Bob Blackman","Harrow East","Bob Blackman","152745"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922378","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-21","<p>There are a number of service recovery and force majeure claims that will have to be processed before officials are able to assess if Arriva Rail North is in contravention of the Franchise Agreement.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-06-21T14:44:39.857Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922378/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922378/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922378/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-12","Northern: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether the number of trains cancelled in April by Arriva Rail North has put it in default on its franchise obligations.","false","Biography information for Ian Mearns","Gateshead","Ian Mearns","152736"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922379","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-21","<p>All franchise agreements contain a standard clause under which train operating companies may approach the Secretary of State with a request for compensation for net losses that arise out of industrial action.</p><p> </p><p>Our records show no compensation payments under this clause have been made to train operating companies since 2006.</p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-06-21T15:11:25.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922379/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922379/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922379/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-12","Train Operating Companies: Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, with reference to the Answer of 15 May 2003 to Question 113237 on rail strikes, whether rail franchise agreements still contain clauses to allow train operators to claim reimbursement of revenues lost as a result of official industrial action.","false","Biography information for Ian Mearns","Gateshead","Ian Mearns","152737"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922380","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-21","<p>As provided for in all franchise agreements, the Secretary of State, in his discretion, may at any time decide to reimburse or ameliorate net losses of the Franchisee arising from Industrial Action (however caused and of whatever nature) in circumstances where the Franchisee has demonstrated to the satisfaction of the Secretary of State that it has taken all reasonable steps to avoid the Industrial Action and that, Industrial Action having nevertheless occurred, the Franchisee has taken all reasonable steps to mitigate its effects.</p><p> </p><p>Our records show no compensation payments under this clause have been made to train operating companies since 2006.</p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-06-21T15:15:02.62Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922380/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922380/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922380/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-12","Northern: Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what provision there is in the current Northern Rail franchise agreement for the train operator to be reimbursed by the government for revenues lost as a result of official industrial action.","false","Biography information for Ian Mearns","Gateshead","Ian Mearns","152738"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922381","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-21","<p>Any such request would be a commercial matter between Arriva Rail North and the Secretary of State. However, no payments have been made under the relevant Franchise Agreement provisions.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-06-21T14:53:14.903Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922381/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922381/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922381/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-12","Northern: Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether Arriva Rail North has asked the Government to reimburse it for revenues lost as a result of industrial action; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Ian Mearns","Gateshead","Ian Mearns","152739"
