"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922397","Department for Education","false","2018-06-15","<p>The Department publishes the number of pupils at the end of Key Stage 4 who achieved the English and mathematics pillars of the English Baccalaureate. Using this we have derived the number and proportion of pupil who did not achieve the Ebacc English pillar and the EBacc mathematics pillar at various threshold levels including at grades 9-5, 9-4 (A*-C) and 9-1(A*-G). This is the closest information published that provides English and mathematics separately for 16 year olds.</p><p> </p><p>The attached tables show the number and percentage of pupils who did not achieve Ebacc pillars for English and mathematics for each of the last 5 years.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2018-06-15T13:14:24.88Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922397/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922397/answer","152640_Number_not_achieving_Ebacc.pdf","152640_Number_not_achieving_Ebacc.pdf","152640_Number_not_achieving_Ebacc","152640_Number_not_achieving_Ebacc","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922397/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-06-12","School Leaving: Basic Skills","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many children have left school without functional (a) literacy and (b) numeracy in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","152640"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922398","Northern Ireland Office","false","2018-06-19","<p>The Government has committed to commissioning a detailed consultative report into the impact of VAT and APD on tourism in Northern Ireland, to recommend how best to build upon the growing success of that sector.</p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2018-06-19T09:47:58.22Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922398/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922398/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922398/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2018-06-12","Tourism: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what recent discussions she has had with Ministers in HM Treasury on the timescale for responses to its consultation on VAT, Air Passenger Duty and Tourism in Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","152673"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922399","Department for Education","false","2018-06-18","<p>The government provides full funding for adults in England to develop the literacy and numeracy skills they need for life and work, and to secure qualifications from entry level up to GCSE.</p><p> </p><p>The Skills for Life Survey, 2011, estimated the literacy, numeracy and ICT knowledge of adults aged 16-64 in England. The estimates of the numbers and percentage of the adult population with different levels for these components for England are in the attached table.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2018-06-18T13:45:19.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922399/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922399/answer","Number_of_young_people_by_skill_level.doc","Number_of_young_people_by_skill_level.doc","152641_Number of apprentices and their salaries","152641_Number of apprentices and their salaries","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922399/answer","Guildford","Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922399/answer/previousversion/63765","Biography information for Anne Milton","60","Education","Education","2018-06-12","Basic Skills","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate his Department has made of the number of adults who have below average functional (a) literacy and (b) numeracy.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","152641"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922400","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-15","<p>No specific assessment has been made. However, using illegal or street drugs during pregnancy, including cannabis, ecstasy, cocaine and heroin, can have a potentially serious effect on an unborn baby and the advice is to avoid these substances.</p><p> </p><p>Advice about alcohol and drugs is available to pregnant women as part of their routine antenatal care. Pregnant women who misuse alcohol or drugs will be put in contact with a midwife or doctor who has special expertise in the care of pregnant women with alcohol or drug problems. They will be able to refer them to an alcohol or drug treatment programme and other organisations that can help.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-06-15T14:59:49.64Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922400/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922400/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922400/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-12","Pregnancy: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment he has made of the effect of substance abuse by women during pregnancy on a child's health.","false","Biography information for Andrew Selous","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous","152681"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922401","Home Office","false","2018-07-04","<p>The Taskforce aims to complete cases within two weeks, some will fall outside due to complexity but the vast majority are done on the day.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-07-04T08:25:25.423Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922401/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922401/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922401/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-12","Immigration: Windrush Generation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many and what proportion of Windrush generation cases reported to the Home Office were completed within the two-week time limit set by his Department.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","152816"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922402","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-06-15","<p>​The UK has a continuing dialogue with the Government of Bahrain in which we raise individual cases. Our Embassy in Bahrain has monitored this specific case and will attend the next hearing. The UK encourages those with concerns about treatment in detention to report these to the relevant human rights oversight bodies. We urge these bodies to carry out swift and thorough investigations. The UK continues to encourage the Government of Bahrain to deliver on its international and domestic human rights commitments.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-06-15T14:33:37.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922402/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922402/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922402/answer","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922402/answer/previousversion/63766","Biography information for Alistair Burt","16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-06-12","Najah Ahmed Yousif","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what reports his Department has received on investigations being carried out by Bahrain’s human rights oversight bodies with respect to the female political prisoner, Najah Ahmed Yousif; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Alex Norris","Nottingham North","Alex Norris","152847"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922403","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-06-15","<p>​We have raised this case at a senior level with the Government of Bahrain. The Foreign and Commonwealth Office and our Embassy in Bahrain continue to monitor Sheikh Ali Salman's case closely. Embassy officials have regularly attended trial hearings. We continue to encourage the Government of Bahrain to deliver on its international and domestic human rights commitments.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-06-15T14:35:12.33Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922403/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922403/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922403/answer","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922403/answer/previousversion/63770","Biography information for Alistair Burt","16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-06-12","Ali Salman","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether his Department has made representations to the Bahraini Government on the prosecution of Bahraini opposition leader, Sheikh Ali Salman; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Alex Norris","Nottingham North","Alex Norris","152848"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922404","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-06-15","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office has provided numerous updates on its programme work in past Human Rights Reports as well as through Freedom of Information Act requests. This information can be found on the gov.uk website.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-06-15T14:37:43.243Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922404/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922404/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922404/answer","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922404/answer/previousversion/63771","Biography information for Alistair Burt","16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-06-12","Bahrain: Technical Assistance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 22 May 2018 to Question HL7775, which Human Rights Reports refer to the Integrated Activity Fund.","false","Biography information for Alex Norris","Nottingham North","Alex Norris","152849"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922405","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-06-20","<p>Yes, we are starting behavioural testing with claimants and health professionals over the summer, followed by a live testing pilot later in the year, which will inform wider rollout decisions</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-06-20T16:31:22.153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922405/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922405/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922405/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-06-12","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether her Department has plans to introduce the video recording of personal independence payment assessments.","false","Biography information for David Simpson","Upper Bann","David Simpson","152704"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922406","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-19","<p>The information requested is not collected centrally.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2018-06-19T10:23:18.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922406/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922406/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922406/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-12","Home Care Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many patients have received homecare help under the NHS in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for David Simpson","Upper Bann","David Simpson","152705"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922407","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-19","<p>The Department has commissioned NHS Improvement to work in collaboration with NHS England on new support arrangements required to help all National Health Service organisations including hospital and ambulance trusts in their responsibilities for ensuring their staff are safe from assaults and abuse. The Government is also supporting new legislation being taken through Parliament that will make assaults and abuse of emergency workers across all public services an aggravated offence.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2018-06-19T13:43:27.123Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922407/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922407/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922407/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-12","Hospitals and Ambulance Services: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what recent steps his Department has taken to ensure the safety of (a) hospital and (b) ambulance staff on duty.","false","Biography information for David Simpson","Upper Bann","David Simpson","152706"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922408","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-06-22","<p>Ministers meet the RSPCA regularly to discuss animal welfare issues. Most recently, Lord Gardiner met them on 11 June 2018. I also attended their parliamentary drop-in on 13 June 2018.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-06-22T09:14:06.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922408/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922408/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922408/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-06-12","Animal Welfare","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, when he last met with representatives of the RSPCA to discuss animal welfare.","false","Biography information for David Simpson","Upper Bann","David Simpson","152707"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922409","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-06-14","<p>Tractor driving courses for 13 to 15 year olds are delivered by private training providers. Information on the number of children that have participated on these courses is unavailable because Defra does not collect data on these courses.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-06-14T15:01:36.61Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922409/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922409/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922409/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-06-12","Tractors: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many children have taken part in the tractor driving for 13-15 year olds course in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for David Simpson","Upper Bann","David Simpson","152708"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922410","Department for Education","false","2018-06-20","<p>The Department has reformed the National Curriculum, to ensure pupils gain a firm foundation in literacy and mathematics, benchmarked against expectations in high performing jurisdictions.</p><p> </p><p>The Department has already seen that literacy and numeracy have improved since 2010. 81% of pupils met the expected standard in the Phonics Screening Check in 2017 up from 58% in 2012. The results of the 2016 Pupils in International Reading Literacy Study (PIRLS) saw England’s nine year old pupils achieving their highest average score since PIRLS began in 2001. These are the first pupils to take part in the PIRLS study since the Government’s education reforms in 2010. In addition, 61% of students reached the expected standard in reading, writing and mathematics at Key Stage 2 in 2017, an increase from 53% in 2016.</p><p> </p><p>To improve standards further, the Department is creating a national network of 35 English Hubs, and a Centre of Excellence for Literacy Teaching, backed by a £26.3 million investment. The hubs will focus on raising standards and sharing effective practice in early language and literacy in reception year and Key Stage 1. We have also established a network of 35 Maths Hubs across the country to lead transformational change in maths teaching from primary to age 18. They are delivering the £74 million Teaching for Mastery Programme which emphasises whole class teaching that builds mathematical knowledge systematically and in depth. Teaching for Mastery will reach over 11,000 primary and secondary schools by 2023.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2018-06-20T16:19:50.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922410/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922410/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922410/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-06-12","Children: Basic Skills","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps he is taken to improve the (a) literacy and (b) numeracy skills of children in England.","false","Biography information for David Simpson","Upper Bann","David Simpson","152709"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922411","Department for Education","false","2018-06-20","<p>The Department for Education does not hold this information. However, data from the Duke of Edinburgh award’s annual report indicates that, in 2017 to 2018, there are 438,329 active Duke of Edinburgh award participants. The annual report also provides more detailed information on the number of new Duke of Edinburgh’s award entrants and the type of centre that they attend. The report can be accessed here: <a href="https://www.dofe.org/statistics" target="_blank">https://www.dofe.org/statistics</a>.</p><p> </p><p>The Department of Culture, Media and Sport (DCMS) and the Big Lottery Fund have committed £1 million to the Duke of Edinburgh’s award scheme via the #iwill Fund. This will help more disadvantaged young people take part in the scheme by supporting individuals, youth groups or the schools that they attend.</p><p> </p><p>The Department for Education is working closely with DCMS to help to ensure that all children and young people can have the opportunity to participate in high-quality programmes such as the Duke of Edinburgh’s award and the National Citizen Service.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2018-06-20T14:45:12.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922411/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922411/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922411/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-06-12","Schools: Duke of Edinburgh's Award Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many schools take part in the Duke of Edinburgh award.","false","Biography information for David Simpson","Upper Bann","David Simpson","152710"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922412","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-06-20","<p>Almost 6,000 mid-tier agreements under Countryside Stewardship (CS) are currently in place. A further 10,500 Mid-Tier applications packs have been requested for agreements that would start on 1 January 2019, an increase of 39% on last year.</p><p> </p><p>Natural England, who currently administer the scheme, have been under severe pressure and this has resulted in delays to the issuing of agreements and the processing of payments. We have been working hard to address this, by, for instance introducing 75% bridging payments to CS agreement holders who have yet to receive either an advance or full payment. Agreement offers for the 2018 period were all issued by end-May, allowing agreement holders to submit their claim by 15th June.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-06-20T16:44:53.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922412/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922412/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922412/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-06-12","Countryside Stewardship Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what assessment he has made of the (a) effectiveness of the introduction of the mid-tier countryside stewardship scheme and (b) the effect of the introduction of that scheme on processing existing (i) entry and (ii) higher level stewardship claims.","false","Biography information for Sir Geoffrey Clifton-Brown","The Cotswolds","Sir Geoffrey Clifton-Brown","152628"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922413","Department for Education","false","2018-06-20","<p>My right hon. Friend, the Secretary of State for Education has not met representatives of the National Union of Students (NUS). As the Minister for Higher Education, I last met the NUS Executive and members of the Senior Leadership team on 22 February 2018.</p><p> </p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2018-06-20T16:25:43.473Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922413/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922413/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922413/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-06-12","National Union of Students","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, when he last met with representatives of the National Union of Students.","false","Biography information for David Simpson","Upper Bann","David Simpson","152711"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922414","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-06-20","<p>The table below outlines the funding per year and the number of projects that Heritage Lottery Fund have awarded to projects in Northern Ireland:</p><p><strong> </strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Financial Year</p></td><td><p>Projects Funded</p></td><td><p>Amount Awarded</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>59</p></td><td><p>£15,029,700</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016-17</p></td><td><p>58</p></td><td><p>£15,155,500</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017-18</p></td><td><p>64</p></td><td><p>£15,617,200</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Grand Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>181</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>£45,802,400</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong> </strong></p>","Northampton North","Michael Ellis",,"2018-06-20T13:46:24.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922414/answer","Biography information for Michael Ellis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922414/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922414/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-06-12","Heritage Lottery Fund: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, how much funding from the heritage lottery fund was allocated to projects in Northern Ireland in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for David Simpson","Upper Bann","David Simpson","152712"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922415","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-06-20","<p>The government has engaged extensively with TV and film production stakeholders on the impact of exiting the EU. Over the past year, DCMS has organised a number of ministerial roundtables as well as bilateral meetings with broadcasters, and television and film production companies on the topic of Brexit and related issues, including the potential effects of our exit from the EU for these companies.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-06-20T13:32:21.693Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922415/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922415/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922415/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-06-12","Film and Television","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what meetings he has held with (a) television and (b) film production companies on the effect of the UK leaving the EU on the UK film and TV industry in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for David Simpson","Upper Bann","David Simpson","152713"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922416","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-06-20","<p>Online gambling operators are required under the Gambling Commission’s Licence Conditions and Codes of Practice (LCCP) to give players the option to set time and spend limits online. The Government is also working with the Gambling Commission on a clear plan to further protect children, young people and the vulnerable as discussed by the Gambling Commission’s review of online gambling in March 2018 (<a href="http://www.gamblingcommission.gov.uk/PDF/Online-review-March-2018.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.gamblingcommission.gov.uk/PDF/Online-review-March-2018.pdf</a>) and the Government’s response to the consultation of changes to gaming machines and social responsibility measures in May 2018 (<a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/707815/Government_response_to_the_consultation_on_proposals_for_changes_to_gaming_machines_and_social_responsibility_measures.pdf" target="_blank">https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/707815/Government_response_to_the_consultation_on_proposals_for_changes_to_gaming_machines_and_social_responsibility_measures.pdf</a> )</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>This will include ensuring operators set limits on consumers’ spending until affordability checks have been conducted; banning operators from providing free-to-play demo games until a consumer’s age has been determined and improving the speed and effectiveness of age verification processes.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>Other measures include tackling unacceptable marketing, advertising and unfair terms and improving complaints and dispute procedures and strengthening requirements to interact with consumers who may be experiencing problems with their gambling and looking at the issue of whether gambling on credit cards should continue to be permitted.</p><p><strong><p><p></strong></p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2018-06-20T13:44:02.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922416/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922416/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/922416/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-06-12","Gambling: Internet","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, if his Department will introduce legislative proposals on limiting the time for which a user can be active on an online gambling site or app.","false","Biography information for David Simpson","Upper Bann","David Simpson","152714"
